     docker commands 

docker pull <imagename> => pull the image from the dockerhub ,registry

docker run <imagename> => pull the image and create and start the container 

docker start <containername> =>start the stop contianer available in local

docker stop <containername> =>stop the running container 
   
docker rm <containername or id> =>remove the container 

docker rmi <imagename> =>remove the image 


docker -p 8000:80 <imagename> => used to port bind with the container to local.
